HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 14
BY REPRESENTATIVE WALTERS
CONDOLENCES: Expresses the condolences of the House of Representatives on the death
of the Reverend Dr. William J. Shaw
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the condolences of the House of Representatives upon the death of the Reverend
3 Dr. William J. Shaw.
4 WHEREAS, it is with immense sadness and profound regret that the House of
5 Representatives of the Legislature of Louisiana has learned of the passing, on March 7,
6 2026, of the Reverend Dr. William J. Shaw; and
7 WHEREAS, the Reverend Dr. William J. Shaw was born in Marshall, Texas, and
8 was the youngest of six children; he was baptized at the age of seven and accepted the call
9 to ministry at an early age; and
10 WHEREAS, Reverend Shaw delivered his trial sermon at the age of eleven and was
11 ordained at the age of seventeen while already serving a small Texas congregation; and
12 WHEREAS, Reverend Shaw graduated summa cum laude from Bishop College at
13 nineteen years old and earned degrees from Union Theological Seminary and Colgate
14 Rochester Divinity School; and
15 WHEREAS, Reverend Shaw became the pastor of White Rock Baptist Church in
16 West Philadelphia in 1956; he guided the one hundred twenty-seven-year-old church for
17 seven decades, making him one of the region's longest-tenured and most influential
18 ministers; and
19 WHEREAS, Reverend Shaw rarely missed a Sunday during his seventy-year tenure
20 and devoted his ministry to nurturing congregants through preaching, mentorship, and
