1 pastoral care; his "Sheepfold Ministry" empowered lay leaders to comfort families, visit the
2 sick, and support one another in the community; and
3 WHEREAS, Reverend Shaw served two terms as president of the National Baptist
4 Convention USA, Inc.; he was recognized for his leadership at the highest levels of
5 American government, and President Barack Obama appointed him to the President's
6 Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships and the United States
7 Commission on International Religious Freedom; and
8 WHEREAS, Reverend Shaw was an incredibly civic-minded individual who made
9 significant contributions to the Philadelphia community; he served as executive director of
10 the Opportunities Industrialization Center and served on the boards of Junior Achievement
11 of the Delaware Valley and Penn Medicine, where he chaired the trustee board of the
12 Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania; and
13 WHEREAS, Reverend Dr. William J. Shaw is survived by his son, Timothy; two
14 granddaughters; and several great-grandchildren; he will be deeply missed, but the legacy
15 of his service shall live on in perpetuity in the hearts and minds of those he served.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
17 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of the
18 Reverend Dr. William J. Shaw and does hereby extend sincere wishes that his family,
19 friends, congregation, and loved ones find comfort in their shared memories of his beautiful
20 life.
